# .dockerignore
#
# What this file does:
# Tells Docker which files to SKIP when copying the build context into the image.
#
# Feynman version:
# When you COPY . . in a Dockerfile, Docker grabs everything in this folder.
# Without this file, that includes things we never want inside a container —
# like local environment secrets, OS junk files, or git history. This file
# is the bouncer at the door saying "you're not on the list" to those files.

.env
.env.*
*.md
.git
.gitignore
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
